http://h3abionet.org/tools-and-resources/sops/16s-rrna-diversity-analysis
^^the above provides a schematic workflow for 16S rRNA analysis--if you hover your pointer over each box in the pipeline, 
it gives one a summary of each step
http://qiime.org/1.2.1/tutorials/tutorial.html
^^pretty comprehensive tutorial explaining how to use qiime 
http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3105689/
^^neat journal article providing an assessment of UniFrac (the distance metric utilized in the beta analysis component) and the 
utility of jacknifing as a sort of check for UniFrac 

Please don't hesistate to add any resources you think may be helpful! :) 
